==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gens
<hw>Gens</hw> <pr>(j⟦ecr⟧nz)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Gentes</plw> <pr>(j⟦ecr⟧n"t⟦emac⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See
<er>Gentle</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Hist.)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A clan or family connection, embracing several families
of the same stock, who had a common name and certain common religious
rites; a subdivision of the Roman curia or tribe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A minor subdivision of a tribe,
among American aborigines. It includes those who have a common descent,
and bear the same totem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gent</ent>⟦br⟧
